Subject: ASK: add CPE_FAST_PATH Kconfig stanza

The CONFIG_CPE_FAST_PATH symbol gates ASK fast-path infrastructure
(brevent notifier types, abm_ff/iif_index/qosmark skb fields, and
several netfilter/bridge/IP-forwarding hookable taps) added by the
ASK patch series. Prior askN iterations relied on a hand-edited
.config setting CONFIG_CPE_FAST_PATH=y, but on mainline 6.18.x's
kbuild, `make olddefconfig` silently drops unknown symbols from
.config, so CONFIG_CPE_FAST_PATH never reached autoconf.h, all
gated code became inert, and the auto_bridge OOT module failed to
compile (struct brevent_fdb_update / BREVENT_PORT_DOWN /
BREVENT_FDB_UPDATE / register_brevent_notifier all missing).

Add an explicit `config CPE_FAST_PATH` stanza in net/Kconfig so the
=y in release/ask.config sticks across olddefconfig.

--- a/net/Kconfig
+++ b/net/Kconfig
@@ -26,6 +26,15 @@
 
 if NET
 
+config CPE_FAST_PATH
+bool "Comcerto/ASK fast-path infrastructure"
+default n
+help
+  Enable the in-kernel surface consumed by ASK out-of-tree modules
+  (auto_bridge, cdx, fci, fp_netfilter): brevent notifier chain,
+  sk_buff fast-path fields (abm_ff, iif_index, qosmark), and
+  hookable taps in net/bridge, net/ipv4, net/ipv6, net/netfilter.
+
 config WANT_COMPAT_NETLINK_MESSAGES
 	bool
 	help
